text: The 1927–28 Eintracht Frankfurt season was the 28th season in the club's football history. In 1927–28 the club played in the Bezirksliga Main-Hessen, the top tier of German football. It was the club's 1st season in the Bezirksliga Main-Hessen. The league was founded with the clubs of the north- eastern part of the Bezirksliga Rheinhessen-Saar merging with those of the Bezirksliga Main (Main division). The season ended up with Eintracht winning the Bezirksliga Main-Hessen (Main division).
